re may be something wrong with the muscles of your smaller hand. Go to see doctor as well if that's the case. <\/p>\n","answer_id":45711,"question_id":45706,"up_vote_count":2}],"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/questions/45706/why-is-the-left-hand-bigger-than-the-right-hand","last_activity_date":1461881831,"creation_date":1461879581,"answer_count":1,"title":"Why is the left hand bigger than the right hand?","body":"<p>I've noticed that the left hand is bigger than the right hand, more precisely - I don't know whether it is really bigger or just more flexible?<\/p>\n\n<p>I compared the hand span of the left hand and right hand and in my case the hand span of the left hand is almost 1cm bigger than the right hand. I've noticed that other people which I asked, had the same thing, sometimes the difference was less in their case.<\/p>\n\n<p>I'm right-handed person, but still the hand span of the left hand is slightly bigger. Does anyone know the reason for this? Are the bones of the left hand for some reason longer? Or is it just a hand span/the flexibility? If so, then why left hand is more flexible?<\/p>\n","question_id":45706,"tags":["bone-biology"],"score":1,"down_vote_count":0,"closed_reason":"primarily opinion-based","is_answered":true,"view_count":37,"up_vote_count":1},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://i.stack.imgur.com/J4tKI.png?s=128&g=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":21835,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/21835/tesgoe","reputation":6,"display_name":"tesgoe"},"closed_date":1461918504,"comments":[{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://i.stack.imgur.com/1sIMq.jpg?s=128&g=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":4108,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/4108/remi-b","reputation":22909,"display_name":"Remi.b","accept_rate":88},"score":1,"post_id":45703,"edited":false,"creation_date":1461877973,"comment_id":80145,"body":"If you <a href=\"https://www.google.ca/webhp?sourceid=chrome-instant&amp;ion=1&amp;espv=2&amp;ie=UTF-8#q=why%20is%20dn