ine  (Knopf et al.,  1978).  From  an  evolutionary  standpoint,  taurine  was plentiful  in  the  diet  of  a  true  carnivore,  as  high  concentrations  of  taurine  are  found  in muscle  tissue. However,  as  most  domesticated  felines  normally  do  not  consume  living\n  prey, they are at risk to become taurine-deficient if not adequately supplied in the diet.<\/p>\n<\/blockquote>\n","answer_id":45680,"question_id":45661,"up_vote_count":2}],"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/questions/45661/which-mammals-cannot-synthesize-taurine","last_activity_date":1461832492,"creation_date":1461774586,"answer_count":1,"title":"Which mammals cannot synthesize taurine?","body":"<p>It is fairly common knowledge that domesticated cats cannot synthesize the compound taurine. Other mammals seem to be able to synthesize taurine from cysteine [<a href=\"https://www.google.com/url?sa=t&amp;rct=j&amp;q=&amp;esrc=s&amp;source=web&amp;cd=14&amp;ved=0ahUKEwi4krWFna_MAhUEx4MKHaAoBzUQFghsMA0&amp;url=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.biochrom.co.uk%2Fdownload%2F35&amp;usg=AFQjCNGw-BVRpJ_UcYFMDrs-Utu5_V5qTQ&amp;sig2=-eyrMIZZVzL5sIDF7WiRow&amp;bvm=bv.120551593,d.amc\" rel=\"nofollow\">source<\/a>]. Are there other mammals that lack the ability to synthesize taurine? <\/p>\n","question_id":45661,"tags":["biochemistry","biosynthesis"],"score":1,"down_vote_count":0,"is_answered":true,"view_count":47,"up_vote_count":1},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/664f03009f3e969c16a0991b84397b17?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG&f=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":23263,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/23263/snivybelinda","reputation":1,"display_name":"snivybelinda"},"closed_date":1461830982,"comments":[{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://i.stack.imgur.com/SjvUL.png?s=128&g=1","user_type":"moderator","user_id":3340,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/3340/wysiwyg","reputation":23153,"display_name":"WYSIWYG","accept_rate":80},"score":1,"post_id":45678,"edited":false,"creat