e: Symptoms in exercise: acute urticaria after 1 min, and arrythmia/moderatePain... after 45 min, which stops exercise. Nothing in ECG/Holter/ECHO. \nAntihistamines contraindicated because of severe anticholinergic effects (dysphonia, ...) even with 3rd gen. Montelukast. Metabolic disorder. 25 year old man. Obese (BMI 30). Eosinophilia. <\/p>\n\n<p>I do not understand the pathways (H1,H2,...) in MD/DMII to the cardiac manifestations which stop exercise. \nHypothesis<\/p>\n\n<ol>\n<li>increased permeability of vessels, vasodilation, decreased HR, decreased CO (SV constant)\n\n<ul>\n<li>where I do not understand $\\Delta$ permeability $\\to$ vasodilation. Hypothesis: histamine intolerance, but still, I do not understand the pathogenesis.  <\/li>\n<\/ul><\/li>\n<li><em>insulin resistance/metabolic syndrome, which increases the risk for atherosclerosis and cardiovascular events, is an aggregate of disorders related to obesity or visceral adiposity, insulin resistance, hyperlipidemia, and hypertension<\/em><\/li>\n<li><em>Because the loss of histamine functions has been suggested to result in disturbed energy regulation and metabolism,6,7,8 we speculated that the functions of histamine might be closely related to the pathogenesis of insulin resistance syndrome, metabolic disturbances, and NASH.<\/em><\/li>\n<li>Metabolic syndrome, histamine intolerance $\\to$ cardiac manifestations.<\/li>\n<\/ol>\n\n<p>where I am wondering how <em>insulin resistance/metabolic syndrome<\/em> is linked to the histamine surges in exercise.  <\/p>\n\n<h2>Sources<\/h2>\n\n<ol>\n<li><a href=\"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC2913336/\" rel=\"nofollow\">Histamine Regulation in Glucose and Lipid Metabolism via Histamine Receptors<\/a>. Model for Nonalcoholic Steatohepatitis in Mice. Am J Pathol. 2010 Aug; 177(2): 713\u2013723.<\/li>\n<\/ol>\n\n<hr>\n\n<p>How can you stabilize histamine surges in Exercise of MD/DMII?<\/p>\n","question_id":45667,"tags":["metabolism","pathophysiology","d