narrowing or complete blockage of the coronary arteries). Angina often results in pain felt in the neck, shoulders, and back rather than in the thorax (chest), which is the actual the site of the injury. <\/p>\n\n<p>A massage-related field of therapy has evolved around this - <a href=\"https://www.painscience.com/tutorials/trigger-points.php\" rel=\"nofollow\">trigger point therapy<\/a>, where trigger points are defined as the cause of pain elsewhere in the body. From personal experience I can add my gratitude to this field of therapy; it's been good to me. <\/p>\n\n<p><a href=\"http://i.stack.imgur.com/f7cqF.png\" rel=\"nofollow\"><img src=\"http://i.stack.imgur.com/f7cqF.png\" alt=\"TP\"><\/a><br>\n<sup>Trigger points. source: <a href=\"https://www.tptherapy.com/images/TriggerPoint/tp_inst2.png\" rel=\"nofollow\">Trigger Point Therapy<\/a><\/sup><\/p>\n","answer_id":45503,"question_id":45502,"up_vote_count":7,"last_edit_date":1461444272},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://i.stack.imgur.com/LBnjL.png?s=128&g=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":22415,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/22415/graham-chiu","reputation":254,"display_name":"Graham Chiu"},"score":14,"is_accepted":true,"comments":[{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://i.stack.imgur.com/Ma6sp.jpg?s=128&g=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":23431,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/23431/qpaystaxes","reputation":101,"display_name":"QPaysTaxes"},"score":1,"post_id":45505,"edited":false,"creation_date":1461432046,"comment_id":79744,"body":"As a side note, transferred pain is actually pretty critical to know about as a ski patroller. To use your example of myocardial ischemia (and, for that matter, infarction) one of the big symptoms in males is pain radiating down the left arm and up into the throat, in some cases reaching as far as the hand, which is pretty far from the heart."},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://i.stack.imgur.com/Ma6sp.jpg?s=128&g=1","user_type":"registered","user_id"